This repository redistributes pre-built binaries in addition to its own
source code. Those binaries carry their own licenses and attribution
requirements, summarized below.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Carbonyl (bundle/carbonyl-linux-x86_64.tar.xz)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The "rich-mode browser" feature ships pre-built Carbonyl binaries — a
terminal-rendering frontend over the Chromium engine.

Upstream Carbonyl (MIT License):
    https://github.com/fathyb/carbonyl

The bundled binary is built from a fork tracking Chromium ~M148:
    https://github.com/nickna/carbonyl  (commit 68012ed8…)
    Chromium SHA: f161c335…

Because the bundle contains compiled Chromium components, it is subject to
the Chromium project's licenses and third-party attribution requirements,
in addition to Carbonyl's own MIT terms.

Chromium is distributed under the BSD 3-Clause License with additional
third-party attributions for hundreds of bundled libraries (V8, ICU, ANGLE,
Skia, FFmpeg, Blink, etc.). The canonical, complete attribution text lives
in the Chromium source tree:

    LICENSE:                 https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/main/LICENSE
    Third-party credits:     https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/main/chrome/browser/resources/settings/about_page/about_page.html
                             (compiled into every Chromium binary; accessible
                             at chrome://credits inside the running browser)

When this product is launched as a browser (the Web lobby entry), the user
can press F1 / open chrome://credits to read the complete Chromium and
third-party license attributions compiled into the binary itself.

